Kaveel Singh, News24(Duncan Alfreds, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Durban - Police are investigating a case of murder after the body of a 30-year-old woman was discovered shot dead on the N2 north just after Spaghetti Junction on Friday."We can confirm that a case of murder will be opened after a 30-year-old woman was found dead on the side of the highway this morning. The motive for the killing is unknown," police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said.Rescue Care spokesperson Garrith Jamieson said a truck driver found the woman."On assessment they found a female who had sustained a single gunshot wound to her upper body. Paramedics assessed her and unfortunately, she had already passed away. She was declared deceased on scene." 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.